If these photos aren’t the definition of ‘keep going’ then I don’t know what is. 

The top photo is from my first show ever in 2012. 6 of my friends piled into a car and drove down to Philly to watch me. I *PAID* $200 to play the show for my 6 friends. My buddy Eric was “DJing” for me on my HP college laptop my Nanny bought for me from Staples. 

It’s wild what things can turn into when you believe in a vision, work your ass off, and stay consistent. We’ve come a long way, through the ups and downs, and still have a long way to go. I appreciate you endlessly for being along for the ride and I am so grateful for your support. So many great things on the horizon. 

Follow your dreams and keep going 💜

P.S. I can’t wait to get back on the road and tear up a stage near you 🎤

If you’re reading this thank you. Thank you for supporting, thank you for listening, thank you for your constant messages, comments, and kind words. Thank you for taking the time to give my music a chance and in turn supporting my dreams. Words can’t express how grateful I am for you and this community we’ve built. You all help me just as much (if not more) as I hope my music helps you. Whatever your dream is, visualize it, set goals, and chase that shit. Keep going, even on the darkest days. That is what you all have taught me. 

I am so excited about what is on the horizon and so poised to take this to the moon. Again thank you, my dream is just some distant idea without you. 💜🌻

PS: Hope to see some of you in Buffalo, Pittsburgh, & DC very soon! A lot more music, content, and shows coming your way in 2024. Love you all 💜

What a year… a lot of learning and growing took place. A lot of ups and downs took place. I’m proud of myself for working through the difficulties and continuing to push forward even when I thought I was running in place. 
Like I read yesterday on a container of sugar at WaWa, “failure is success in progress.” Very grateful for all that happened this year, but I am the most grateful for everyone that supported. Thank you so much for being here and I am so excited for what lies ahead. 
Next year, same shit… chasing my dreams. I hope you do the same 💜🌻 

Happy NYE y’all 🥂
